column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED SAMPLE 0-2M
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
10% white cumulus clouds.  Water mildly choppy.  North wind 8-10 MPH.  1.1" rainfall yesterday.  Moderate boat traffic.
20% White cumulus clouds.  Water mildly choppy.  W wind 8-10 MPH.  Cold front went thru yesterday.  Moderate boat traffic.
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
35% white cumulus clouds.  Dead calm.  2nd beautiful day without rain.  Very few boats on lake.  Lake bloom showing at shoreline.
30% white cumulus clouds.  Water mildly choppy.  W wind 8-10 MPH.  Moderate boat traffic.  Light lake bloom throughout the lake.

Unable to take readings for 6 days due to constant rain (over 4" in 4 days).  Clouds and strong winds today.  Low overcast completely- but fairly bright light conditions.  Light chop. S wind 5-7 MPH. Very few boats.
Low overcast with occasional bright spots.  Very light water chop.  1-3 MPH northwest wind.  No boat traffic.
Clear- blue sky- north wind at approximately 6 mph- and trees leave almost a peak color.
10% cloud cover- mostly blue sky- 5 mph south easterly winds- approximately 8 boats on the lake- and 60% of the leaves are off the trees.
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
Partly cloudy sky- wind out of the southwest at 10 mph- one boat on the lake- and saw a young loon.
Complete thin overcast- however- quite bright. Water mildly choppy. 8-10 mph North wind. Cold front going through. No boat traffic.
90% overcast. No direct sunlight. Water quite choppy. 12-15 mph South wind. Showers off to west and south. Moderate boat traffic. Warm and humid.
5% white cumulus clouds- bright sunlight. Wate mildly choppy. 8-10 mph north wind. Moderate boat traffic. Nice day. Warming up. Very heavy airborne pine pollen throughout area.
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
Light overcast. Hazy sunshine. Water quite choppy. 12-15 mph south wind. Very humid. Warm. Light rain overnight. Boat traffic moderate.
20% white cumulus clouds. Bright sunlight. Water very choppy. 12-18 mph southwest wind. Light boat traffic. Very hot and humid.
Clear blue sky. Light 5 mph south wind. Moderate boat traffic.
Cloudy sky. Thunder storm approaching. Light 5 mph southwest wind. 1.4" rainfall in morning.
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
Sunny- 5% cumulus clouds. Water mildly choppy. 5-8 mph west wind. Moderate boat traffic. Very hot and humid. Storms on previous nights.
Sunny- clear sky. Water quite choppy. 12-18 mph southwest wind. Moderate boat traffic. Temperature in the low 80's.
Bright sunlight- 50% high thin cirrus clouds. Water mildly choppy. 8-12 mph south wind. Past 4 days strong winds with large waves on lake. Moderate boat traffic.
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
Bright sunlight- 5% cumulus/cirrus clouds. Very little water chop. 3-5 mph south wind. Little boat traffic.
Bright sunlight. Very light haze. Almost totally clear sky. Water quite choppy. 10-15 mph west wind. Moderate boat traffic. Heavy rain on 9/5. Gloomy cloudy threatening weather 9/6.
Sunny clear sky. Water fairly choppy. 8-10 mph south wind. Very light boat traffic.
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
Slightly hazy. 15% cumulus clouds. Very light west breeze. Extremely light water chop.  Temperature near 70 F. Very little boat traffic.
Sunny/partly low cumulus clouds (50%). East wind 10-15 mph.  Medium to light water chop - temperature near 70F. Light boat traffic.
Totally clear- cloudless sunny day.  Southeast wind 10-15 mph.  Medium water chop.  Temperature 75-80 F. Seaplane took off and landed on lake.  Moderate boat traffic.

Occasionally sunny- 80% low cumulus clouds (some dark).  Quite a bit of boat traffic.  Last 2 days rainy- windy- very cold (couldn't take reading).  Strong NW wind 20-25 mph. Water very choppy. Temperature 64 F.
Total low cloud overcast.  Light 20-25 mph NW wind.  Very light water chop.  Temperature near 60 F. Very little boat traffic.
2-5% scattered clouds - variable 2-3 mph breeze.  Very light water chop.  Temperature near 60 F. Very little boat traffic.
50% low cumulus clouds. 5-8 mph North wind.  Light water chop. Very strong northerly winds yesterday causing rough waves all day.  Temperature about 70 F.  Moderate boat traffic.
90% low overcast.  10-18 mph north wind.  Considerable water chop.  Temperature near 70 F.  Light boat traffic.  Difficult to see into water.
50% low cumulus clouds. Hazy sunshine.  12-18 mph south wind.  Heavy water chop.  Temperature low 80s.  Saw one sailboat. Moderate boat traffic. Humid.
100% low overcast. No sun or wind.  Lake flat. Tempearture 75 F.  No boat traffic. Very light rain about 1:00 pm.
15% low cumulus clouds.  5-8 mph west wind. Medium water chop.  Temperature 62 F.  Light boat traffic.  Stronger winds earlier in the day.
Cloudless sky with slight haze.  Light westerly breeze. SMall ripples on lake surface. Temperature 80 F. Light boat traffic.  Light green scum along shoreline.
50% low cumulus clouds- 6-8 mph west wind- medium water chop- 65F- very little boat traffic
30% low cumulus clouds- 2-5mph West wind- light water chop- temp. low 70'S- very light boat traffic
60% cumulus clouds- 10-15 mph NW wind- fairly heavy water chop- temp. 58F (it's been really windy and below 60F for days) (where is the global warming effect ) light boat traffic
25% low cumulus with some high sirus clouds- hazy- 3-5mph SE breeze- light water chop- 76F- light boat traffic
20% low cumulus with patches of high sirus clouds- light NE breeze- water almost calm- 80F- scattered surface algae- heavier near shore- light boat traffic
50% low cumulus clouds- 10-15mph west wind- fairly heavy water chop- temp 65F- a front went through last night with no rain- light boat traffic
50% low cumulus clouds- 8-12mph west wind- mediumwater chop- considerable overnight rain- temp 68F- moderate boat traffic
low overcast mixture of clouds with occasional openings- 8-15mph SE wind- considerable water chop- temp. 70F- light boat traffic- humid
80% low cumulus layered clouds- (some very dark)- 6-12 mph- W wind- mild water chop- temp. 68F- light boat traffic- light rain last 24 hours
almost solid overcast with occasional small openings to emit filtered sunlight- very light south wind- very small lake chop- temp. 70F- light boat traffic- humid
10% low cumulus clouds with streaks of high sirus clouds- 5-12mph W wind- light to medium water chop- temp. 80F- moderate boat traffic- somewhat humid
90+% dark low clouds.  7-10 mph- south wind.  Light to medium water chop.  Temperature 76 F.  Very little boat traffic.
Almost totally clear sky.  10-15 mph.  Northeast wind 10"-15" waves.  Temperature 68 F.  A lot of small particles suspended in water.  Light boat traffic.  Third successive windy day.
60% rather dark cumulus clouds - 2-4 mph west wind.  Light water chop.  Temperature 68 F.  Light boat traffic.  Rain storm with wind overnight.
Total overcast of low dark clouds - 10-15 mph north wind.  8"-12" waves.  Temperature 58 F.  Fir amount of boat traffic.
Less than 5% scattered white cumulus clouds.  3-6 mph north wind.  Fairly light water chop.  Temperature 78 F.  Quite havey boat traffic.
15% high cirrus clouds not blocking sun.  8-12 mph southwest wind.  6"-10" water chop.  Temperature 78 F.  Light boat traffic.
About 50% patches of white cumulus clouds.  6-12 mph northwest wind.  4"-8" water chop.  Temperature 76 F.  Moderate boat traffic.
About 50% patches of fluffy white cumulus clouds.  10-15 mph west wind.  8"-10" water chop.  Temperature 74 F.  Light boat traffic.
About 80% low dark cumulus clouds.  15-25 mph.  Southwest wind 12"-15" waves (a few whitecaps).  Temperature 80 F.  Only saw one other boat.  Very strong winds yesterday too.
clear sunny day- few small clumps of white clouds- 4-6mph SW breeze- very light water chop- no boat traffic- Temp. 78F
100% Fairly light overcast- fair light penetration- 6-10mph W wind- moderate water chop- light boat traffic- temp 73F
75% partial cloud cover (some high- some low) 6-12mph W wind- moderate water chop- rained in early morning- temp 75F- (heavy boat traffic- jet-skis and pontoons)
clear sunny day- 5% high thin sirus clouds- very light southwest breeze- light ripples on surface- temp 80 F- very little boat traffic
Mostly sunny- 40% thin high sirus clouds- few low small clumps of white clouds- 3-8mph west breeze- light water chop- no boat traffic- temp 80F
clear sunny day- no clouds- 0-2mph south breeze- small ripples on surface- temp 70F- too windy to test lake yesterday- very light boat traffic
Mostly sunny- about 5% mixture of small clumps and high wind blown sirus clouds- 5-7mph SW wind- light water chop- temp 80F- very little boat traffic
Partially bright sunny day- 40% low white cumulus clouds- very light west breeze- light ripples on surface- temp 70F- very light boat traffic
bright clear sunny day- 5% thin high separated sirus clouds on NW horizon- very light W breeze- temp 77F- very small surface ripples- moderate boat traffic
Bright clear sunny day- cloudless- 3-5mph light north wind- 2" to 3" ripples on surface- temp 65F- very little boat traffic
Clear sunny day - very few small white cumulus clouds.  8-10 mph south wind.  Medium water chop.  Very little boat traffic.  Temperature 80 F.
Clear sunny day.  Very few small white cumulus clouds.  8 mph south wind.  Light water chop.  Very little boat traffic.  Temperature 77 F.
Total overcast but fairly bright.  8-12 mph south wind.  Medium water chop.  Some boat traffic.  Light rain early morning.  Temperature 64 F.
Clear sunny day.  About 20% low clumps of white cumulus clouds.  Very light south breeze.  Water level very low.  Considerable algae.  Temperature 75 F.  Lake almost flat.  Very little boat traffic.

Bright sunny day.  About 40% low clumps of white cumulus clouds.  Variable 1-3 mph breeze.  Water level very low.  Considerable algae at shoreline.  Very light water chop.  No boat traffic.  Temperature 81 F.
Bright sunny day.  About 50% high thin stratus clouds.  Variable 1-3 mph breeze.  Very light water chop.  Very little boat traffic.  Water level still very low.  Temperature 83 F.
Total overcast gray day.  6-10 mph southeast wind.  Medium water chop.  No boat traffic.  Temperature 61 F.  Water level still very low.  Last 2 days strong winds with white caps.

Bright sunny day.  about 25% low clumps of cumulus clouds.  6-8 mph north wind.  Fair amount of shoreline algae.  Water level still very low!  Medium water chop.  Light boat traffic.  Temperature 69 F.
80% low fairly thin overcast.  4-6 mph west breeze.  Light water chop.  Very little boat traffic.  Temperature 71 F.  Water level still very low!
Total overcast grey day. 8-12 mph south wind. Medium water chop. Very little boat traffic. Temperature 62 F. Water level extremely low!
40% clumps of white puffy low cumulus clouds- plus western half high thin stratus clouds.

column1: Temperature 56 degrees- very light boat traffic
8-12 mph north wind- moderate water chop

column2: 50% thin stratus clouds- balance cloudless; dead calm- bright- temperature 63 F.  7 boats still fishing- 2 eagles in flight.
60% large stratus clouds (some large and high and darkening).  Wind west 10-15 mph.  6 to 8" water chop - temperature 70 F.  2 boats in sight.  1 eagle soaring.
Moderate solid overcast.  Fairly bright.  Few raindrops.  West wind 8-12 mph.  6 to 7" water chop.  Temperature 76 F.  4 boats in sight.
40% clumps of white cumulus clouds- otherwise blue sunny sky- south wind 7-10 mph.  3 to 5" water shop.  Temperature 72 F- 1 boat- 1 jet ski in sight.
80% low cumulus (some white- some dark)- southwest wind 10-15 mph with higher gusts- 6" to 8" water chop - temperature 72 F- 1 boats- 1 jet ski in sight.
50% moderate sized white cumulus clouds- otherwise sunny.  Northwest wind 4-6 mph.  2-3" water chop.  Temperature 69 F.  Heavy boat and jet ski traffic (10+ units).
70% scattered high thin sirrus clouds.  Southwest wind 12-15 mph.  5 to 7" water chop.  Temperature 76 F.  7 boats in sight.
100% totally clear blue sky.  South by southwest breeze.  4 to 6 mph.  3" water chop.  Temperature 74 F.  5 fishing and 1 pontoon boat.  1 eagle dropped down to pick up a fish.
50% moderate sized white and grey cumulus clouds.  North by northwest wind 3-6 mph.  2-3" water chop.  Temperature 74 F.  2 boats in sight.
80% low cumulus and 100% high stratus clouds (no sun). 1 -2 MPH breeze from northeast. small ripples;temperature 64 degrees. 10 boats anchored. Occassional sprinkles.
8% low light cumulus clouds. Sunshine. 10-13 MPH wind from west. Temperature 79 degrees. Very few boats on lakes. Lake level up 11 inches in 10 days - good!

Totally clear- blue sky. Fairly strong north wind 15-18 MPH. Chop - 6-8 inches. Temperature 62 degrees. Several boats in sight. Lake level just about normal after 5.25 inches of rain in 20 days.  Mostly clear sky- about 30% cumulus clouds. 6-10 MPH north wind with 6 inch water chop. Temperature 74 degrees. Six boats in sight. Lake level about normal. Mostly clear sky- about 30% cumulus clouds. 6-12 MPH north wind. 6 inches water chop. Temperature 74 degrees. Six boats in sight. lake level about normal.
35% white fluffy cumulus clouds. Sunshine- 12-16 MPH wind from west. Water chop 4 to 6 inches. Temperature 76 degrees. 5 boats in sight. Lake level about normal.
15% scattered low cumulus clouds. 8-12 MPH west wind. Water chop 6-8 inches. Temperature 76 degrees. 3 boats. jet skis in sight. lake level slightly low. Eagle cruising shoreline at length.
Total moderate overcast (can bearly see shadows). Almost dead calm. Temperature 82 degrees- very humid. 8 boats in sight- several pontoons. Typical dog day of August day.
Totally clear- blue sky. Gusty wind- 7-10 MPH from the south. Water chop 6 to 10 inches due to several jet skis and large boats pulling inflated tubes. 6 boats in sight- none anchored.

35% very high cirrus clouds- 5% low scattered cumulus clouds near horizon to the northeast. Variable 6-12 MPH north wind. Water chop 4 to 8 inches. Temperature 75 degrees. 4 boats in sight. pleasant early fall day.
5% small clumps scattered clouds. Strong 15 to 20 MPH west wind. Water chop 8-10 inches. Temperature 62 degrees. No boats in sight. Sunny.
50% white fluffy cumulus clouds - bright - wind 3 to 7 mph from west - 2" to 3" water chop - temp. 83 degrees - 5 boats in sight - 1 soaring eagle
100% low cloud cover - wind 2 to 4 mph from the north - 1" to 2" water chop - temp. 61 degrees - 3 boats in sight - 2 loons in sight
50% clumps of cumulus clouds - bright sun on + off- wind 10 to 14 mph from north - 6" to 8" waves - temp. 67 degrees - 6 boats in sight
50% clumps of cumulus clouds - bright sun on + off - dead calm - temperature 78 degrees - lake level normal - 8 boats in sight
100% cloud cover - beginning to rain-wind 10 to 12 mph from south - temp. 68 degrees - 2 boats in sight
30% clouds - light 4 to 6 mph south wind - temp. 80 degrees - lake level normal - 8 boats in sight
100% overcast fairly high clouds - very light 2 to 4 mph south wind - 1" to 2" water chop - temp. 72 degrees - lake level normal - 3 boats and 1 jet ski in sight
90% layers of cumulus + high sirus clouds - wind 4 to 6 mph from southwest - 2" to 3" water. chop - temp. 74 degrees - 6 boats in sight (one pontoon)

wind 20 to 25 mph from west - 8" to 12" waves - temp. 75 degrees - no boats in sight - 95% low rain clouds (through small break in clouds could see very little blue sky + high sirus clouds) - some light rain showers
85% scattered low cumulus with high sirus above (peaks of sun) - no appreciable wind - neglegible water chop - temp. 70 degrees - 4 boats in sight (1 pontoon)
1 to 2% very small clouds - winds 10 to 15 mph from west - 4" to 6" water chop - temp. 78% - 3 boats in sight (1 pontoon)
60% white/grey low cumulus clouds - north winds 3 to 5 mph - 2" to 4" water chop - temperature 68 degrees - 5 boats in sight (one pontoon)
10% scattered white cumulus clouds - southwest wind 8 to 14 mph - 3" to 6" water chop - temperature 80 degrees - 9 boats in sight (one pontoon)
clear blue sky- north breeze 1 to 3 mph - small ripples - temperature 74 degrees - 4 boats (2 pontoons) beautiful day
50% scattered white cumulus clouds and high scattered stratus clouds - north breeze 2 to 5 mph - 2" to 4" water chop - temperature 85 degrees- hot and humid! 4 boats in sight (3 pontoons)
15% scattered white and grey cumulus clouds/ mostly sunny- north wind 6 to 10 mph - 3" to 5" water chop - temperature 75 degrees - 5 boats in sight (1 pontoon)
5 to 10 % high- thin scattered cumulus and higher wisps of stratus clouds - west wind 15 to 20 mph - 5" to 7" waves- a few white caps - temperature 88 degrees- 3 boats in sight (1 pontoon)
5% scattered small clumps of cumulus clouds (mostly clear sky) - calm- temperature 84 degrees- 5 boats in sight (1 pontoon and 1 canoe) nice day

80% low scattered cumulus clouds (mostly white- some grey) - wind 5 to 7 mph from west - 2" to 3" water chop - temperature 78 degrees- 5 boats and 4 jet skies in site- sun behind lare- fairly dark cloud
total overcast with sun's location visable - dead calm- temperature 69 degrees - 1 pontoon- 1 jet ski and 1 large fishing boat in sight
50% scattered white cumulus clouds - west wind 8 to 12 mph - 3" to 6" water chop - temperature 78 degrees- 2 boats in sight - overcast morning- now clearing
several small clumps of white cumulus clouds - southwest wind 3 to 5 mph - very small water chop - temperature 85 degrees- saw 1 loon- 2 pontoon boats and 2 small row boats in sight

almost total overcast of 50% low dark cumulus and much higher grey stratus clouds with occassional break through of dull sun - east wind 5 to 8 mph 3" to 6" water chop - temperature 78 degrees - 2 fishing boats in sight
50% scattered white cumulus clouds- SW winds 5 - 10 mph. 3" to 5" water chop. Temperature 65 f. 3 Boats in sight. Nice cool day.
2 to 3 % high stratus and cumulus clouds. SW Wind 2 to 4 mph. Small water chop. Temperature 68 f. 6 boats in sight. Nice cool day.
Overcat day with occasional periods of rain. NW wind 12 to 15 mph. 8" to 12" water shop. Temperature 69 f. No boats in sight.
15% high thin clouds. Very calm 1 to 2" water chop. Temperature 76 f. 4 boats in sight- very nice day.
95% low cumulus clouds. West wind 15 to 18mph. 3" to 5" of water chop. Temperature 68.5 f. 2 kayaks and 2 boats in sight. Seagulls flying over lake.
95% low cumulus clouds- west wind 15-18 mph. 3" to 5" water chop. Temperature 68.5f. 2 fishing boats- 1 jet ski- 4 sea gulls in sight.
Overcast day- NW wind 6 to 8 mph. 2" to 4" water chop. Temperature 57f. 3 fishing boats- 3 sea gulls- 2 ducks in sight on water.
50% clumps of low white cumulus clouds. W wind 8 to 10 mph. 3"  to 5" water chop. Temperature 64.8 f. 2 Fishing boats- 1 jet ski- 3 sea gulls- 2 ducks in sight on water.
Totally clear- west wind 3 to 6 mph. Temperature 84 f. 4" to 6" water chop. 4 fishing boats- 1 loon- 9 seagulls in sight on water.
60% high stratus clouds. NW wind 2 to 4 mph. Temperature 78 f. 2 to 3" water chop. 5 fishing boats- 2 pontoon boats- 18 seagulls in sigh on water.
50% cloudy- wind W 15mph- 4 fishing boats- 1 pontoon boat
45% cloudy- wind N 8 mph- 3 fishing- 1 boat- 1 ski boat
90% cloudy- 2 fishing boats- wind SW- 2 adult and 2 chick loons
20% cloudy- wind NW 10 mph- 3 fishing boats
20% cloudy. 3 fishing boats. 2 loons. Wind out of the north at 7 MPH.
Sunny. 2 fishing boats. wind out of the south southwest at 20 MPH.
100% cloudy. 4 fishing boats. wind out of the south at 6 MPH.
90% cloud cover. Wind out of the southeast 5 MPH. 11 boats on the lake.
30% cloud cover. 7 fishing boats. Wind out of the south at 3 MPH.
6% cloud cover. 3 fishing boats. 1 tuber. Wind out of the north 8 MPH.
2% cloudy. Wind out of the south at 8 MPH. 3 pontoon boats. 1 jet skier. 2 ski boats.
30% cloud cover. Wind south west. 2 pontoons- 1 fishing boat. 3 gulls.
wind out of the south at 11 MPH. 5% cloud cover. 3 ski boats and 1 jet ski.
Sunny-64F- pair of loons- 1 eagle- 1 fishing boat- high cirrus clouds- 4-5" chop- wind 15mph
air 64F- mostly cloudy- windy- 3 fishing boats- 2 speed boats- 4-5" waves
Partly cloudy- air 75F- 2 ski boats- 3 fishing boats- loon w/2 chicks

Air 84F- Humid- mostly cloudy- 5-10 mph SW wind- 3-4" waves- 1 boat fishing- 1 tubing- 3 loons- 3 gulls
Air 78F- wind 5-10 mph- cumulus clouds- 4 boats fishing- 1 jet ski- 3 gulls
Air 78F- sunny- windy WSW- 6-8" white caps- High clouds- 3 boats fishing- 1 skiing- 4 loons- 1 eagle- 1 gull
